{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Judgment Awaiting Thrice Guilty Israel

\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
For Israel\uc1\u8217*s three crimes \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
no, four! \uc1\u8211* I will not rescind my judgment.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
They sell the righteous for money,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
the needy for a pair of shoes.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}They trample on the head of the poor,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
push the humble out of the way.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Father and son go to the same temple girl,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
and so profane my holy name.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}They stretch themselves on garments taken in pledges beside every altar,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
and they drink the wine of those who have been fined in the house of their God.      
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}It was I who destroyed the Amorites for your sake,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
whose height was like that of the cedars,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
as strong as oaks.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
I destroyed their fruit from above and their roots from below.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 10}It was I who brought you up from the land of Egypt,       
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
and led you forty years in the wilderness,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
and brought you here to possess the land of the Amorites.    
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}I raised up some of your sons to be prophets
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
and some of your youths to be Nazirites.
\par}

